                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.&#8212;<name type="person" key="130">Private
                        Thomas Morrissey</name>, <name type="organization" key="87">Co. A, 2d
                        Vermont Volunteers</name>, aged 26 years, was admitted to <name
                        type="hospital" key="176">Lincoln Hospital</name>, Washington, <date
                        type="admit" when="1863-04">April, 1863</date>, under the charge of <name
                        type="person" key="131">Surgeon H. Bryant</name>, <name type="organization"
                        key="132">U. S. Volunteers</name>, on account of a contusion of the head.  Symptoms of arachnitis were manifested; but the patient recovered partially, was
                    transferred to a <name type="hospital" key="xx">convalescent camp</name> near
                    <name type="place">Alexandria</name>, on <date type="transfer" when="1863-03-10">March
                        10th</date>.  He was discharged from service on <date type="servicedischarge"
                        when="1863-03-20">March 20th, 1863</date>. His mental faculties were much
                    impaired. His disability was rated at two-thirds.   <name type="person" key="132">Surgeon S. B. Hunt</name>, <name type="organization" key="132">U. S. V.</name>, records the case. </p>            
